    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName>Hitcham, Bildeston, Suffolk</placeName>
                        <date>21 Janr 1840</date>
                        <salute>My dear Sir,</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>I must apply for another pennyworth of information. Can you give me any information about your Neuropteris Loskii plate 49 which if <hi rend="underline">correct</hi>, is, as Sternbergh says "a N. L. Brongniartiani distinctissima. Now I have before me specimens from Felling Colliery which approach Brongniart's pl.72. fig.1. very closely but do not at all correspond to your fig. There is a sort of stiffness about the fig. which makes me suspect it was not drawn by a botanical eye, &amp; that it has been somewhat <hi rend="underline">beautified</hi>. Have you a fragment of the species which you can let me see. There seems to be a mess about these species which I can't quite unravel without authenticated specimens - your N. heterophylla of plate 183 seems very difft. from those at 197 &amp; 200 &amp; is not referred to at the latter places. I am longing for your named specimens to clear away a few other doubtful points.</p>
                        <p>Yrs very truly</p>
                        <p>J. S. Henslow</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
